## Week 1 — Day 3 | Prometheus Queries + Data Exploration

```bash
# Forward Prometheus to localhost
kubectl port-forward -n monitoring svc/monitoring-kube-prometheus-st-prometheus 9090:9090

# Forward Grafana to localhost
kubectl port-forward -n monitoring svc/monitoring-grafana 3000:80

# Commit Prometheus query reference
git add .
git commit -m "docs: add Prometheus query reference for CPU, memory and pod metrics"
git push
```

**PromQL queries run:**
```promql
# CPU usage per node
100 - (avg by(instance) (rate(node_cpu_seconds_total{mode="idle"}[5m])) * 100)

# Memory usage per node
(node_memory_MemTotal_bytes - node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes) / node_memory_MemTotal_bytes * 100

# Pod count per node
count by (node) (kube_pod_info)
```

**Result:** Cluster producing live metrics. Nodes at ~2% CPU, ~54% memory. Queries saved to `docs/prometheus_queries.md`.

